<br>
about rangers:  ranger dps is higher than wizards when they use true shot.  true shot can't be used on every fight because of reset time.  also, rangers are oftened unable to shoot things at all when mob is pinned certain ways. <br>
<br>
other int casters: wizards generally have a wider more mana efficient selection of spells to choose from.  examples, necros are famous for their inefficient DD spells, and chanters are basicly limited to Magic based nukes.<br>
aggro and chain casting:  a wizard that knows what he is doing can maximise his damage on a mob by chain casting.  i've done this and been able to keep myself off aggro.  the biggest nerf against my dps (so far as i can tell) was the change that now prevents an instant clicky from resetting my gems.  nonetheless, i can still do a consistantly high amount of damage.  it doesn't matter what resist type the mob is, where it gets pinned, or if i have some skill up.<br>
