<br>
Wizards come out pretty good in the end picture, if that's what you're asking.  All this stuff above is assuming similar aa/gear, blah blah, and it's based on parses I did while I was playing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elyia>Elyia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 286<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/7/03 7:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Best Damage Dealing Class in the high end game?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>ranger dps is higher than wizards when they use true shot. true shot can't be used on every fight because of reset time. also, rangers are oftened unable to shoot things at all when mob is pinned certain ways. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
