<br>
Pets were very unreliable because of Fear. Players were unreliable too, but they tended to get the damage in better.<br>
<br>
&gt;They upgraded CT and Inny a month or two before we would have been ready to fight them so I dont know.<br>
<br>
They were much easier to hit and were only level 55. I never had a lot of problems on either, and of course once Kunark came out and you could level to 60, they were real easy since they were Dark Blue mobs til they changed them.<br>
<br>
&gt;Sky.. I suspect mages and wizards are competitive there, and there's nothing wrong with that really. Sky is a screwy place though, even given a relatively small amount of competition within my guild in the first place, in Sky there seemed to be even less. Sky always seemed to me to encourage team spirit. <br>
<br>
Mages had an edge in Sky until Lures got in the game, because you couldn't hit some of the mobs with normal spells, but pets still worked. But Sky wasn't hit as much as Hate/Fear/Dragons til after Kunark came out and it became more doable. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4380">Qaman</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
